IO/File/Lockable version 0.30
=============================

IO::File::flock is extended IO::File for flock, it corresponds by many systems.
IO::File::fcntl is extended IO::File for fcntl, it correspond to NFS.
and IO::File::Lockable is a base class for locking a file.

SYNOPSIS

use IO::File::flock;
my $fh = new IO::File::flock($finame,'>');
my $fh = new IO::File::flock($finame,'<');
my $fh = new IO::File::flock($finame,'>>');
  or
use IO::File::fcntl;
my $fh = new IO::File::fcntl($finame,'>');
my $fh = new IO::File::fcntl($finame,'<');
my $fh = new IO::File::fcntl($finame,'>>');

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  IO::File
  Fcntl

